Of the 74 patients, 30 (40%) patients had ECS or ICS lesions. A total of the 37 lesions (Tables 1 and 2
) were identified in these 30 patients (Figure 1
). Seven patients had both ECS and ICS lesions, 15 patients had only ECS lesions and 8 patients had only ICS lesions. Of the 37 lesions, 21 (28.4%) were symptomatic (13 ECS and 8 ICS) and 16 were asymptomatic.
